FBIS3-10062 "drlat040_m_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 Brazil Transport Minister Coimbra Submits Resignation PY0103020294 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in Portuguese 2300 GMT 28 Feb 94 PY0103020294 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] Transport Ministry Margarida Coimbra today submitted a note of resignation to President Itamar Franco, but she has not yet received a reply to her request. Coimbra is being pressured to leave her post. Last week the newspaper O GLOBO reported that Coimbra's husband, Carlos Henrique Siqueira, had tried to use his influence to obtain a release of funds for construction work on the Rio de Janeiro-Niteroi bridge. The work is being carried out by the Noronhe Engineering Company, for which Siqueira works.
